1
00:00:06,010 --> 00:00:08,558
♫ I want to go to the future ♫

2
00:00:08,558 --> 00:00:12,213
♫  Time bears witness to my quirkiness  ♫

3
00:00:12,213 --> 00:00:18,306
♫  I want to seize the day and put the whole world into my head  ♫

4
00:00:18,306 --> 00:00:24,532
♫  I want to go back in time to do all the crazy things I didn't do  ♫

5
00:00:24,532 --> 00:00:30,753
♫  Don't say goodbye, don't be in a daze, let my radiant light be bright  ♫

6
00:00:30,753 --> 00:00:36,039
♫  We are always looking forward to the unknown future  ♫

7
00:00:36,039 --> 00:00:43,206
♫  And often overlooking our surroundings and best plan in front of us  ♫

8
00:00:43,206 --> 00:00:48,363
♫  Every day my heart beats for you  ♫

9
00:00:48,363 --> 00:00:49,776
♫  Be your light  ♫

10
00:00:49,776 --> 00:00:55,739
♫  You are no doubt irreplaceable  ♫

11
00:00:55,739 --> 00:01:02,139
♫  Every day the sun shines through the window  ♫

12
00:01:02,139 --> 00:01:08,606
♫  With your reflection being my incredible highlight  ♫

13
00:01:08,606 --> 00:01:11,759
[I Don't Want to be Brothers with You]

14
00:01:11,759 --> 00:01:14,059
I'm not going to the company today.

15
00:01:14,079 --> 00:01:16,280
I told you my son is back home now!

16
00:01:16,280 --> 00:01:19,099
Just do your job. Don't ask me about everything!

17
00:01:19,099 --> 00:01:20,380
Yang Yang.

18
00:01:20,380 --> 00:01:22,099
We'll talk later.

19
00:01:22,099 --> 00:01:23,680
Yang Yang, sit down for breakfast.

20
00:01:23,680 --> 00:01:25,131
Come on.

21
00:01:28,519 --> 00:01:30,030
Hurry up and eat.

22
00:01:44,120 --> 00:01:45,868
Do these suit your taste?

23
00:01:51,339 --> 00:01:52,560
Yang Yang,

24
00:01:52,560 --> 00:01:54,640
you've been in Beijing for a while.

25
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:57,380
You've been busy with school and haven't had time to walk around.

26
00:01:57,380 --> 00:02:00,440
Your mom and I have time today.

27
00:02:00,440 --> 00:02:02,659
Let's go walk around Beijing, okay?

28
00:02:03,139 --> 00:02:06,300
I heard you were fond of Beijing since you were a child.

29
00:02:06,300 --> 00:02:08,080
Let's go visit Tian'anmen first.

30
00:02:08,080 --> 00:02:10,319
Then, we'll go to the zoo.

31
00:02:10,319 --> 00:02:13,260
The zoo? He's too big for the zoo.

32
00:02:13,260 --> 00:02:17,839
Then let's go to Wangfujing (famous shopping district) and buy some clothes for Yang Yang.

33
00:02:19,619 --> 00:02:21,194
That's not necessary.

34
00:02:22,000 --> 00:02:22,919
You should go.

35
00:02:22,919 --> 00:02:27,060
You see, Yang Yang came in a hurry this time and didn't bring a lot of clothes.

36
00:02:27,060 --> 00:02:28,759
This is your mom's good intentions.

37
00:02:28,759 --> 00:02:30,724
She wants to spend some time with you.

38
00:02:32,420 --> 00:02:33,819
Why don't you guys just buy some for me?

39
00:02:33,819 --> 00:02:37,060
I'm fine with anything. It's all up to you.

40
00:02:41,619 --> 00:02:44,760
I'll go check on the oatmeal first.

41
00:02:54,580 --> 00:02:58,000
Gao Yang, who are you pulling a long face for?

42
00:02:58,800 --> 00:03:00,903
- I'm not.
- You're not?

43
00:03:02,580 --> 00:03:04,542
I know.

44
00:03:04,542 --> 00:03:10,279
You miss Gao Bin, right? You miss that Ye Xiaowen, and your cronies, right?

45
00:03:14,700 --> 00:03:16,719
Here's the phone. Call them.

46
00:03:18,619 --> 00:03:21,020
I'm letting you use it. I told you to call them.

47
00:03:21,020 --> 00:03:22,339
Go ahead.

48
00:03:22,339 --> 00:03:23,800
Act normal after you call them.

49
00:03:23,800 --> 00:03:25,140
No one owes you anything.

50
00:03:25,140 --> 00:03:26,650
Mom,

51
00:03:29,048 --> 00:03:30,860
I'm not thinking about contacting them.

52
00:03:30,860 --> 00:03:33,936
I promised you I would go abroad and I'll do what I say.

53
00:03:41,860 --> 00:03:43,722
Gao Yang,

54
00:03:44,379 --> 00:03:46,800
I'm not trying to fight with Gao Bin for you.

55
00:03:46,800 --> 00:03:49,539
I just want you to have a bright future.

56
00:03:49,539 --> 00:03:53,960
It's fine if you go to the end of the world and be as far away from me as possible.

57
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:57,247
I'm used to not having you around over the years anyway.

58
00:04:03,080 --> 00:04:04,942
Mom, don't worry.

59
00:04:04,942 --> 00:04:06,903
I will go abroad.

60
00:04:07,460 --> 00:04:09,539
I'm going to study now.

61
00:04:31,090 --> 00:04:32,839
Beibei!

62
00:04:32,839 --> 00:04:34,679
Beibei!

63
00:04:42,399 --> 00:04:43,639
Xiaowen?

64
00:04:43,639 --> 00:04:46,060
Let's go. Time for school.

65
00:04:46,639 --> 00:04:48,217
Coming.

66
00:04:51,219 --> 00:04:56,899
"Though we had buried Belikov, there are still many such men in cases.

67
00:04:56,899 --> 00:05:00,099
How many more of them there will be?" (The Man in a Case by Anton Chekhov)

68
00:05:00,099 --> 00:05:02,040
I've recited this text for you.

69
00:05:02,040 --> 00:05:03,319
We all know that

70
00:05:03,319 --> 00:05:08,519
Chekhov was a famous Russian litterateur, novelist, and playwright.

71
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:10,752
I've told you

72
00:05:16,519 --> 00:05:18,839
about the three great masters of

73
00:05:18,839 --> 00:05:21,839
short stories in the world.

74
00:05:21,839 --> 00:05:22,800
Who else did we talk about?

75
00:05:22,800 --> 00:05:26,919
Chekhov, Maupassant, who's the third one?

76
00:05:26,919 --> 00:05:28,879
Which one of you knows?

77
00:05:29,960 --> 00:05:32,260
Xiaowen, you answer it. Who's the third one?

78
00:05:32,260 --> 00:05:33,279
O. Henry.

79
00:05:33,279 --> 00:05:34,160
That's right.

80
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:37,060
We've talked about this. Remember them, okay?

81
00:05:41,859 --> 00:05:43,879
- Bin.
- You're here.

82
00:05:46,380 --> 00:05:48,360
Why are you here again?

83
00:05:49,219 --> 00:05:51,221
What is it?

84
00:05:51,221 --> 00:05:54,700
Do you think I'm shutting myself out and being depressed?

85
00:05:54,700 --> 00:05:58,960
I'm not. Look at this ball, I'm polishing it really nicely.

86
00:05:58,960 --> 00:06:02,260
The kids will be happy to see it, right?

87
00:06:02,260 --> 00:06:04,220
It is very shiny.

88
00:06:05,600 --> 00:06:07,580
It... it's pretty shiny.

89
00:06:10,500 --> 00:06:12,399
Wait, why are you here?

90
00:06:12,399 --> 00:06:13,924
Tell me.

91
00:06:20,530 --> 00:06:24,539
What do you think about Gao Yang going abroad?

92
00:06:26,940 --> 00:06:28,987
What else can I think?

93
00:06:28,987 --> 00:06:30,960
I wish him all the best.

94
00:06:30,960 --> 00:06:32,843
Go send him off before he leaves.

95
00:06:34,959 --> 00:06:36,420
I'll approve two days of leave for you.

96
00:06:36,420 --> 00:06:38,360
Go see him in Beijing.

97
00:06:38,360 --> 00:06:39,820
That's not necessary.

98
00:06:39,820 --> 00:06:45,000
Xiaowen is still here. He's about to compete. I can't leave.

99
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,720
I think Xiaowen is in a good state.

100
00:06:46,720 --> 00:06:48,800
He even asked Beibei to go to school together this morning.

101
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:50,639
What do you know?

102
00:06:50,639 --> 00:06:52,339
Stop polishing it.

103
00:06:52,339 --> 00:06:54,099
He's really upset inside.

104
00:06:54,099 --> 00:06:56,855
He's just pretending to be strong, you know?

105
00:06:57,360 --> 00:06:58,899
Besides,

106
00:06:59,519 --> 00:07:01,669
